	   <tr><td colspan=2>For the most part, this sounds like very good advice.&nbsp;&nbsp;But I have to question the last comment...<br><br>I'm not sure that dungeons are so bad.  I would say being careful with your AE songs would be the only thing to worry about.  I typically do not use Selo when fighting, only for pulling and travel, and I easily solo blues and whites.  I can even solo the occasional yellow if it is the right kind of creature.<br><br>Of course, much of this probably depends on stats and equipment.  I'm only mildly twinked at level 9, nothing outrageous (less than full armor - best piece Lockjaw Hide Vest).  But I do play a Vah Shir, and I put my bonus points into DEX, STR, and STA at creation.  This has been the easiest character to solo with that I have ever played.<br><br>With the EXP bonus offered by most dungeons, I would not rule them out just because you cannot use Selo.  Especially if you have good STR, STA, and DEX and decent equipment.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
