<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101017245996774></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101017245996774><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101017245996774>RE: Bardo Numero Uno?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101017245996774#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=126085><span id=Scholar>The Honorable MentalSword</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>44 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jan 4th 2:27 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.42]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi all.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have just started my first Bard, who is a Vah Shir.  While this is my first attempt with a Bard personally, I have had several friends with Bards in the past and so have a good feel for how they should play.<br><br>I have to say, I REALLY like the Vah Shir Bard!!!  Their naturally high dex is perfect for the Bard.  A fairly high strength and stamina also make the beginning solo levels easier.  The only trade off the is lower charisma.  I, personally, have a specialized plan for my Bard, and am going to leave the mezzing up to the Enchanters.  I therefore did not spend many bonus points on charisma.  I bolstered my dex, str, and sta primarily.<br><br>I realize this is kinda of a unique creation for a Bard, but one could just as easily leave the default 90 str of the Vah Shir and spend most points on chr and dex.<br><br>I am also VERY fast.  And in fact, I guess that a Vah Shir Bard is the fastest possible character in the game, given the Bard's ultimate speed buff.  At levels 1-4 I could easily pull most mobs near to a guard without taking damage during the run back.  Now at level 5, with my speed song, I can outrun much higher level characters who have SoW.<br><br>Shar Vahl is a nice newbie city.  It is easy to navigate, contains all of the appropriate shops for a young Bard, and has plenty of mobs for reaching level 4.  There are also great starter quests for each class available to the Vah Shir.  As a Bard, you be able to get some armor and craft your first drum (and this is necessary as the local instrument merchant does not carry and percussion instruments).<br><br>Also, Shadeweaver's Thicket (right outside of Shar Vahl) is another great low-level zone.  You've got a much wider range of monster levels, plenty of guards, merchants, and even a bank!<br><br>All-in-all I think the Vah Shir is an excellent choice for a Bard.  Especially for a nontraditional Bard such as my own.  =)<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
