<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100907626477782></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100907626477782><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100907626477782>RE: Bardo Numero Uno?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100907626477782#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=967><span id= >Clarion</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>9 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 22nd 9:57 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've no experience related to Vah Shir Bards, that's what I was Looking for when I came to this page.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, I can comment on Wood Elf and Half Elf Bards.<br>Wood Elves have a lot of advantages as a young Bard, with natural Hide and Forage, plus good nightvision.   They also have the highest Total stats of the Bardic races.  However, their weakness in Strength can be a problem.  Still, being able to wear the Small size of the various armors does cut down on the total weight they're forced to bear, which is a small blessing.<br>Half Elves have fewer Total stats, but the Distribution of those stats is near Bard-perfect.  Bards don't really need all of that Wisdom...  Unfortunately, being Medium-only diminishes that advantage, at least in the begining.  Also, not having Hide at a young age, or Forage, makes growing up a bit more expensive, and their nightvision is less acute, too.<br><br>I love my Main, a Wood Elf Bard of the 37th Canto and my low-level Half Elf Bard is turning out to be a lot of fun, due to some minor twinking.  Now I'm considering a Vah Shir, and I just can't seem to convince myself that any of the other Classes would be better, given the abilities of the Cat-men.  Besides, I Love being a Bard.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
