	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Dec 20th 6:03 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.32]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello all!<br><br>I'd like to pass along a great tip!<br><br>Are you sick and tired of turning on Selo's whenever you run? Wouldn't you just like to run and have it start automatically? Me too... Here's how:<br><br>1) Click and hold down your mouse button on your Selo's song on your spell bar. Soon it will &quot;float&quot; onto your cursor.<br><br>2) &quot;Drop&quot; Selo's into one of your macro boxes (usually on the left side of your screen unless you've customized it). I use box #5, so I'll use that in this example.<br><br>2) Go to OPTIONS, then KEYBOARD. Go NEXT until you get to USER IDENTIFIED #5. (Use the entry that corresponds to the box you put Selo's in)<br><br>3) Right click on the secondary slot for this key (the bottom of the pair), then press your Up Arrow button.<br><br>Voila!!! Now, whenever you press the Up Arrow key to move forward in the game, you start Singing Selo's!<br><br>The only downside is that when you stop running and press Up Arrow again you are, in effect, stopping the song.<br><br>By the way, this is also a GREAT way to keep that pain-in-the-butt-but-oh-so-useful SENSE HEADING maxed! Drop it in a different macro box and map it to the Up Arrow key too.<br><br>If you don't want to see the SENSE HEADING messages after it maxes (and it will sooner than you think) just go back into OPTIONS, KEYBOARD and take it off! What could be easier?<br>&nbsp;<br>Botten Baggens<br>6 Earthen Lane<br>Rivervale<br>Saryrn<br><br>Galius Dalmatius<br>N. Freeport<br>Saryrn</td></tr>
